The Director General of the Nigeria Mining Cadastre Office (MCO), Engr. Obadiah Simon Nkom has said the agency is eliminating speculators from mines field and giving their licenses to serious investors. Engr. Nkom stated this when he received a Monitoring Team from the Ministry of Budget and National Planning on the implementation of the 2018 budget appropriation. “The agency is enforcing ‘Use it or lose it’ principle to eliminate speculators and thereby freeing areas in the mines field for serious investors. The principle is aimed at discouraging investors holding on to license acquired without putting it to use,” Nkom said in a statement OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. CLICK HERE TO KNOW MORE He expressed the agency’s commitment to accountability and transparency in implementing capital projects. He pointed out that the mandate of the Ministry is to bring in investors and generate more revenue for government through the MCO. “Mining is capital intensive and we need investors to increase government’s revenue for the development of the country,” he said. Earlier, the Team leader of the group, Ndana Abudurazaq explained their mission to the Agency which is basically to monitor the implementation of the 2018 budget appropriation to MCO. The team inspected all procured items appropriated under the 2018 budget.  Mining Cadestral Office issued 7000 licenses in 8 years — DG How solid mineral roadmap in boosting Nigeria’s revenue FG restates commitment to secure lives of miners Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin